# Virtual Machine Inventory
This document lists all planned virtual machines, their roles, operating systems, and network placement. All VMs run on the gaming PC hypervisor.

---

## 1. Core Infrastructure

### DC01 – Domain Controller
- OS: Windows Server (2019 or 2022)
- Role: Active Directory Domain Services, DNS
- Network: LAN-Core
- Notes: Primary identity provider for the lab

### FS01 – File Server
- OS: Windows Server
- Role: SMB shares, lab storage, permissions testing
- Network: LAN-Core
- Notes: Used for NTFS/ACL practice and centralized storage

### MGMT01 – Management Workstation
- OS: Windows 10 or Windows 11
- Role: Administrative jump box
- Network: LAN-Core
- Notes: Runs RSAT tools, RDP, SSH, browser-based management

---

## 2. Monitoring and Security

### LOG01 – Monitoring / SIEM Server
- OS: Linux (Ubuntu Server recommended)
- Role: Syslog collection, SIEM, dashboards
- Network: LAN-Core
- Notes: Receives logs from ER605, Tenda, Windows servers, and clients

---

## 3. Client Systems (Windows Only)

### WIN-CLIENT01 – Windows Client
- OS: Windows 10 or Windows 11
- Role: Domain-joined workstation
- Network: LAN-Core
- Notes: Used for GPO testing, login scripts, software deployment

### WIN-CLIENT02 – Secondary Windows Client (Optional)
- OS: Windows 10 or Windows 11
- Role: Additional test workstation
- Network: LAN-Core
- Notes: Useful for multi-user or multi-device testing

---

## 4. Guest/IoT Network Simulation

### GUEST-LINUX01 – Guest Network VM
- OS: Lightweight Linux distro
- Role: Simulated IoT/guest device
- Network: Guest/IoT (behind Tenda router)
- Notes: Used to test isolation and firewall rules

---

## 5. Future VM Ideas
- WSUS server for Windows updates
- Dedicated DNS filtering server (Pi-hole or AdGuard)
- Web server for internal testing
- Vulnerable VM for security practice
- Backup server (Veeam, UrBackup, etc.)
